modules.description: This module handles the conversion and manipulation of attribute lists, primarily used for interacting with Amazon SimpleDB. It provides functions to parse XML nodes into attribute lists, convert attribute lists to query parameters or JSON representations, and construct attribute lists from JSON input. Use cases include preparing data for SimpleDB queries and processing query responses.

This module defines a type `t` representing an invalid query expression error response from Amazon SimpleDB, containing an optional `box_usage` field for metering information. It provides functions to construct, parse, and convert the type to and from query parameters, JSON, and XML formats. This module is used to handle error responses when querying SimpleDB with malformed or unsupported query expressions.

This module handles the result of retrieving attributes from a SimpleDB item. It provides functions to create, parse, and convert attribute results to query or JSON formats. It works with attribute lists and is used when processing responses from SimpleDB get requests.

This module handles lists of AWS SimpleDB items, providing direct conversions to and from XML, JSON, and query formats. It includes parsing from XML nodes, constructing empty item lists, and transforming item lists into AWS query parameters or JSON structures. Concrete use cases include processing AWS SDB responses, building requests with multiple items, and serializing item data for storage or transmission.

This module handles the result of listing domains in Amazon SimpleDB, providing functions to create, parse, and convert domain name lists with optional pagination tokens. It works with domain names as a list structure and supports serialization to and from JSON and query formats. Concrete use cases include processing responses from domain listing operations and handling paginated results when retrieving domain names from SimpleDB.

This module handles lists of deletable items in AWS SimpleDB, providing functions to convert item lists to and from XML, JSON, and query formats. It supports operations for parsing item data from XML nodes and serializing item lists into query parameters or JSON structures. Use this module when managing batch deletions or attribute updates in SimpleDB domains.

This module defines a type `t` representing error responses for exceeding domain attribute limits in a database service, with an optional `box_usage` field indicating resource consumption. It includes functions to construct, parse, and serialize the error data to query parameters or JSON format. Use this when handling or reporting quota exceeded errors from database operations involving domain attributes.

This module defines a request structure for deleting attributes from an item in a domain. It includes operations to create, parse, and serialize the request in JSON, XML, or query format. It is used when issuing delete attribute commands to Amazon SimpleDB, optionally applying update conditions.

This module defines a single data type `t` representing a request to delete a domain, containing a `domain_name` field. It provides functions to construct, parse, and convert the request to various formats including JSON and query parameters. Concrete use cases include preparing and serializing domain deletion requests for AWS SimpleDB operations.

This module defines a data structure representing the result of a domain metadata query in Amazon SimpleDB. It includes fields for item counts, size metrics, and timestamps, all with optional values. Operations include creating instances, parsing XML responses, converting to query format, and serializing to and from JSON.

This module defines a data structure for creating a domain in Amazon SimpleDB, containing a single required field: the domain name. It provides functions to construct the request, convert it to query parameters or JSON, and parse it from XML or JSON input. Use this when interacting with AWS SimpleDB to create new domains programmatically.

This module defines a data structure for representing items in a database, with support for encoding and decoding operations. It works with XML, JSON, and query string formats, enabling seamless data interchange. Concrete use cases include serializing items to HTTP query parameters, parsing item data from XML responses, and converting items to or from JSON for storage or transmission.

This module defines a data structure for representing items that can be replaced in a database, consisting of a name and a list of replaceable attributes. It provides functions to construct, parse, and convert these items to query parameters or JSON format. Use this module when managing item updates in a database, particularly for serializing and deserializing item data during API interactions.

This module defines a batch put attributes request structure with operations to create, parse, and serialize the request. It works with domain names and lists of replaceable items, primarily for interacting with Amazon SimpleDB. It is used to prepare and transform batch attribute updates for transmission over HTTP or for processing JSON responses.

This module handles lists of string attributes, primarily for interacting with Amazon SimpleDB. It provides functions to convert these lists to and from JSON and query formats, and to parse them from XML nodes. Use cases include preparing attribute names for batch operations or processing query responses in AWS integrations.

This module defines a deletable item structure with a name and optional attribute list, providing operations to create, parse, and serialize items to query parameters, JSON, or XML. It works with string types, attribute lists, and JSON or XML data representations. Use this module when interacting with AWS SimpleDB to delete items or prepare deletion requests in API calls.

This module defines the structure and operations for constructing and handling Select requests in a database query system. It provides functions to create, parse, and convert Select request data, which includes query expressions, pagination tokens, and consistency flags. Use this module when interacting with database query APIs that require structured request formatting for execution.

This module defines a type `t` with an optional `box_usage` float field and provides functions to create, parse, and convert instances to and from XML, JSON, and query formats. It works with AWS SDB error responses, specifically handling missing parameter errors. Use this module when interacting with Amazon SimpleDB to manage errors related to missing request parameters.

This module defines a single type `t` representing a request for domain metadata, containing a `domain_name` field. It provides functions to construct, parse, and serialize the request to query parameters or JSON, as well as conversion from JSON. It is used when retrieving metadata about a domain in Amazon SimpleDB operations.

This module defines a single type `t` representing a request timeout response from Amazon SimpleDB, containing an optional `box_usage` field that tracks service usage metrics. It provides functions to construct, parse, and serialize timeout values in various formats, including XML, JSON, and query parameters. This module is used to handle timeout responses when interacting with SimpleDB operations like query or get requests.

This module handles the `NumberSubmittedAttributesExceeded` error type from AWS SimpleDB. It provides functions to construct, parse, and serialize the error data, which includes an optional `box_usage` float value. Use this module when interacting with AWS SDB operations that may return this specific error, such as batch attribute updates exceeding service limits.

This module defines a type `t` with an optional `box_usage` float field and provides functions to create, parse, and convert the type to and from XML, JSON, and query formats. It handles error responses related to invalid parameter values in AWS SimpleDB operations. Concrete use cases include processing API errors and constructing error responses for invalid input parameters.

This module defines a data structure for handling invalid number predicates in AWS SimpleDB, primarily used to capture and manage floating-point usage metrics. It includes operations to construct, serialize, and convert instances to and from XML, JSON, and query formats. Concrete use cases include processing and transmitting numeric constraint violations in AWS SDB API requests and responses.

This module defines a type for attributes that can be replaced in a database, with operations to create, parse, and convert these attributes to query parameters or JSON. It works with string and boolean values wrapped in specific type constructors. Use this module when managing update operations for database records that require replacement semantics.

Handles lists of domain names for Amazon SimpleDB operations. Provides functions to convert domain name lists to and from XML, JSON, and query parameters. Used when managing domain name collections in requests and responses.

This module handles the `NumberItemAttributesExceeded` error type from Amazon SimpleDB, primarily for tracking resource limits related to item attributes. It provides functions to construct, parse, and serialize the error data, which includes an optional `box_usage` float indicating AWS service usage. Use this module when handling or reporting SDB errors related to exceeding item attribute limits, especially for error logging, debugging, or custom error handling workflows.

This module handles lists of replaceable attributes in AWS SimpleDB operations. It provides functions to convert attribute lists to and from XML, JSON, and query formats. Use it when managing item attributes for batch updates or queries in SimpleDB.

This module defines a type `t` representing an error response for a non-existent domain in Amazon SimpleDB, with an optional `box_usage` field indicating server resource consumption. It includes functions to construct, parse, and convert the error type to and from XML, JSON, and query formats. Concrete use cases include handling and propagating domain-not-found errors in SDB client implementations.

This module defines a data structure for handling invalid number value test responses in AWS SimpleDB. It includes operations to create, parse, and serialize the structure to query parameters or JSON, primarily working with optional floating-point values. It is used to process and return error responses related to invalid numeric data in SDB operations.

This module defines a data structure for specifying item attributes to update in a domain, including the domain name, item name, attributes to replace, and an optional condition. It provides functions to construct, serialize, and parse these update requests in various formats such as JSON and query strings. It is used when modifying item data in a SimpleDB domain with conditional updates.

This module defines a request structure for retrieving item attributes from a domain, including fields for domain name, item name, optional attribute names, and consistent read flag. It provides functions to construct, parse, and convert the request to query or JSON formats. Use this module when interacting with AWS SimpleDB to fetch specific item attributes with optional consistency controls.

This module defines a request structure for listing domains in a database service, supporting pagination through an optional maximum domain count and a next token. It provides functions to construct, serialize, and convert the request to and from JSON and query formats. Use this module when interacting with domain listing operations that require parameterized requests for pagination or result limiting.

This module defines a type `t` representing an error case where an attribute does not exist in Amazon SimpleDB, containing an optional `box_usage` field for tracking request throughput usage. It provides functions to construct, parse, and convert the error type to and from XML, JSON, and query formats. Use this module when handling or responding to `AttributeDoesNotExist` errors in SimpleDB operations, such as querying or deleting attributes.

This module defines a type and conversion functions for a batch delete attributes request in a domain. It works with a domain name and a list of items to delete, enabling serialization to and from JSON, query format, and XML parsing. It is used to construct and manipulate requests for deleting multiple item attributes in bulk.

This module defines a type and associated functions for handling the `TooManyRequestedAttributes` error response from Amazon SimpleDB. It includes operations to create, parse, and convert the error data to and from XML, JSON, and query formats. The primary use case is to manage error responses when exceeding the limit on requested attributes in a SimpleDB query.

This module represents the result of a Select operation in Amazon SimpleDB, containing a list of items and an optional token for pagination. It provides functions to construct, parse, and convert results to and from XML, JSON, and query formats. Use this module when handling responses from database queries that require processing returned records and managing pagination tokens.

This module defines a data structure for representing attributes in Amazon SimpleDB, including their names, values, and optional alternate encodings. It provides functions to construct, parse, and convert these attributes to and from XML, JSON, and query formats. Concrete use cases include handling item attributes during database queries, updates, and data serialization tasks.

This module defines a type `t` representing an error response from AWS SimpleDB when an invalid next token is provided, containing an optional `box_usage` field for AWS billing information. It includes functions to construct, parse, and convert the type to and from XML, JSON, and AWS query format. This module is used to handle and propagate invalid pagination token errors in AWS SimpleDB API interactions.

This module defines a type `t` representing an error response when domain byte limits are exceeded in a database service, containing an optional `box_usage` field for resource consumption metrics. It provides functions to construct, parse, and convert the type to and from XML, JSON, and query formats. This module is used to handle and propagate error details related to domain size limits during database operations.

This module handles lists of replaceable items for AWS SimpleDB operations. It provides functions to convert item lists to and from XML, JSON, and query formats, enabling direct manipulation of database entries during API interactions. Use this module when constructing or parsing batch updates or queries involving multiple replaceable items in AWS SimpleDB.

This module defines a type `t` with an optional `box_usage` float field and provides functions to create, parse, and convert the type to and from query parameters, JSON, and XML. It is used to handle duplicate item names in Amazon SimpleDB operations, specifically for managing metadata related to request pricing and usage. The module supports serialization and deserialization for communication with AWS SDB APIs.

This module handles the AWS SimpleDB error response when the number of submitted items exceeds the service limit. It provides a data structure with an optional `box_usage` field representing the AWS compute usage metric. Functions include creating, parsing, and converting the error data to and from XML, JSON, and query formats for use in API interactions.

This module defines a data structure for representing update conditions in a database operation, specifically for handling conditional updates based on the existence and value of a named field. It supports creating, parsing, and converting conditions to query parameters or JSON format, enabling integration with API requests that require conditional logic. Concrete use cases include enforcing optimistic concurrency control and applying updates only when specific field constraints are met.

This module defines a type `t` with an optional `box_usage` float field and provides functions to create, parse, and serialize instances. It handles XML, JSON, and query parameter formats for a specific AWS response structure. Use this module when interacting with AWS SimpleDB operations that return number domain exceeded errors, to process or construct the corresponding error payloads.

This module handles the deletion of multiple attributes from items in a domain. It works with `BatchDeleteAttributesRequest` to send HTTP requests and processes responses, returning unit on success or parsing specific AWS errors. Use it to efficiently remove several attributes from one or more items in a single call.

This module handles the creation of a domain in Amazon SimpleDB by defining the input and output types for the operation, along with functions to serialize requests and deserialize responses. It works with the `CreateDomainRequest` type for inputs and handles errors via the `Errors_internal` type, mapping HTTP responses to success or failure states. Concrete use cases include sending properly formatted HTTP requests to create a domain and processing the resulting responses or errors from AWS.

This module handles retrieving attributes from a domain, working with `GetAttributesRequest` and `GetAttributesResult` types. It translates requests to HTTP queries and decodes responses, including errors. Use it to fetch item attributes from Amazon SimpleDB with proper request signing and response handling.

This module defines a comprehensive set of error cases specific to AWS SimpleDB operations, including validation failures, authentication issues, and service limits. It provides functions to convert errors to HTTP status codes, strings, and back, enabling precise error handling and reporting. Use cases include interpreting failed API responses, debugging client requests, and enforcing correct input constraints in AWS SDB interactions.

This module handles listing domains in Amazon SimpleDB by converting requests into HTTP format and parsing responses. It works with input and output types defined in `Aws_sdb.Types` for domain listing operations. Use this module to send ListDomains API requests and decode the results or handle errors specific to domain listing.

This module handles the deletion of a domain in Amazon SimpleDB by providing functions to construct and interpret HTTP requests and responses. It works with the `DeleteDomainRequest` type for input and returns a unit output upon successful domain deletion. Concrete use cases include removing a domain to clean up resources or reset data storage in AWS SDB.

This module provides operations for managing attributes and items in a distributed database system, supporting creation, deletion, and conditional updates with structured data types like replaceable attributes, items, and batch operation containers. It handles domain metadata, query parameters, and error conditions such as service limits or invalid requests, while enabling serialization to XML, JSON, and query formats for API interactions. Use cases include processing batched item modifications, enforcing update constraints, tracking resource usage via metrics, and handling domain-level operations like deletion or metadata queries.

Performs deletion of attributes from items in an Amazon SimpleDB domain. Accepts a domain name and item name along with optional attribute constraints, issuing a signed HTTP request to remove the specified attributes. Useful for cleaning up or modifying item data in a SimpleDB table directly.

This module handles sending requests to update or replace attributes associated with an item in Amazon SimpleDB. It encodes `PutAttributesRequest` values into properly formatted HTTP queries and processes responses, returning `unit` on success or decoding specific AWS errors. It is used when modifying item data in a domain, ensuring correct request signing and error handling for failed updates.

This module handles batch updates of attributes for items in Amazon SimpleDB. It accepts a list of attribute changes per item and sends them in a single request, ensuring efficient bulk modifications. The primary operations convert input data into an HTTP request and parse responses or errors from the server.

This module handles metadata operations for a domain in a database service, providing functions to send and parse HTTP requests and responses. It works with domain metadata requests and results, along with internal error types. Concrete use cases include retrieving domain metadata, signing requests with the correct version, and converting between HTTP and native types for domain metadata operations.

This module handles the conversion of Select requests to HTTP requests and responses back to results or errors. It works with SelectRequest and SelectResult types, along with internal error types for handling AWS SDB select operations. It is used to encode queries for AWS SDB and decode the corresponding XML responses into structured results or typed errors.

This module implements core data manipulation and management operations for Amazon SimpleDB, providing functions to create, delete, and query domains and their attributes. It works with structured types like `CreateDomainRequest`, `GetAttributesResult`, and `BatchPutAttributesRequest` to handle item attributes, domain metadata, and batch operations. Concrete use cases include bulk attribute updates, domain creation and deletion, fetching item data with proper request signing, and handling AWS-specific errors during database operations.
